# Goals

---

## i18n-G1 Internationalization framework supports English and Chinese
**Status:** implemented
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:i18n
**Depends on:** UiSystem-G1

- [x] `vue-i18n` integrated in `frontend/src/i18n/index.ts`
- [x] Locale files loaded from `frontend/src/i18n/locales/{en,zh}.json`
- [x] Locale detection from `localStorage` or browser language
- [x] `setLocale()`/`toggleLocale()` helpers exported
- [x] `fallbackLocale: 'en'` configured

## i18n-G2 All user-facing strings externalized to locale files
**Status:** in_progress
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:i18n
**Depends on:** i18n-G1

- [ ] Audit all views/components for hardcoded strings
- [ ] Ensure new UI features add keys to both `en.json` and `zh.json`
- [ ] Add i18n lint check in CI

Most strings are externalized, but ad-hoc hardcoded text still appears in some newer components.

## i18n-G3 Runtime language switch without page reload
**Status:** implemented
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:i18n
**Depends on:** i18n-G1

- [x] `setLocale()` updates reactive locale and `html lang` attribute
- [x] Components re-render with new translations automatically
